As an interim option before adding launching with attached debugger, a while loop on Debugger.IsConnected can be used to wait for the user to manually attach a debugger. Passing a flag through to Main on startup would allow this:

```
    public static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        if (args.Contains("waitfordebugger"))
        {
            do
            {
                System.Threading.Thread.Sleep(100);
            } while (!System.Diagnostics.Debugger.IsAttached);
        }

        Application.Run<AtomicMain>(args);
    }
```
